    <title>PEEKW</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>page PEEKW PEEKW Function <programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">X<sp/>=<sp/>PEEKW(address)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Reads a <bold>16-bit word</bold> from <computeroutput>address</computeroutput> and returns it as an integer (0–65535).</para>
<para><blockquote><para>[!IMPORTANT] The full 2-byte span must be valid and mapped, or <computeroutput>Bad Address at &lt;address&gt;</computeroutput> is raised. </para>
</blockquote></para>
<sect2 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_PEEKW_1autotoc_md103">
<title>&lt;/blockquote&gt;</title>
<sect3 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_PEEKW_1autotoc_md104">
<title>How to read it</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Loads 2 bytes, <bold>little-endian</bold> (<computeroutput>low</computeroutput> at <computeroutput>address</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>high</computeroutput> at <computeroutput>address+1</computeroutput>).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Unaligned reads are allowed.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_PEEKW_1autotoc_md106">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Read<sp/>a<sp/>16-bit<sp/>word</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">W<sp/>=<sp/>PEEKW(&amp;100020)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>W</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="md_docpages_basic_language_reference_functions_integer_PEEKW_1autotoc_md108">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Match the width to the device register size for MMIO.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
